BDD is the method that extends TDD principles to focus on the desired behavior of the software from the user's perspective

emphasizes collaboration b/n stakeholders, devs and testers to define/understand the expected behavior of the system

scenarios are written in a human readable format which makes requirements more explicit and less ambiguous

'gherkinis' is a specific language used in BDD and test automation tools
  follow a 'Given When Then' structure



BDD process
  discovering requirements
  writing scenarios
  automating scenarios
  executing and verifying
  feedback and refinement


cucumber - testing framework for BDD and acceptance tesing